CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1771963514
OL,3,C'Hero' teen died trying to save friend
OL,4,Cfrom train
OL,6,FA teenage boy who died trying to save
OL,7,Fhis friend from being hit by a high-
OL,8,Fspeed train has been labelled a "hero".
OL,10,FJoshua Myers, from Handforth, and his
OL,11,Ffriend Jordan Everett, from High Lane
OL,12,Fin Stockport, both died when they were
OL,13,Fhit by a train at Poynton Railway
OL,14,Fstation in Cheshire on 3 July 2025.
OL,16,FAn inquest into the two 16-year-old's
OL,17,Fdeaths at Cheshire Coroner's Court
OL,18,Fheard that Jordan desperately tried to
OL,19,Fsave Joshua by "rugby tackling" him
OL,20,Foff the tracks as train approached at
OL,21,F110mph.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
